title.narrative: Women's Entrepreneurship Support Sector Development Program

description.narrative: The program enables women entrepreneurs and micro, small, and medium-sized enterprises (MSMEs) in Armenia to play a greater role in economic development. The program has two components: (i) a policy-based loan to help fund budget allocations to strengthen the business environment and the Small and Medium Entrepreneurship Development National Center (SME DNC) of Armenia; and (ii) a financial intermediation loan (FIL) to enable participating financial institutions (PFIs) to provide local currency loans to MSMEs, of which at least 50% are women's MSMEs. The program is supported by capacity development TA to improve the entrepreneurial capacity of women and to increase the capacity of the SME DNC. The implementation period is 2013-2017.
